Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and finely chop @yellow onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped). Core, seed, and remove ribs from @green bell pepper{1}(cored, seeded, and finely chopped). Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Mince @jalapeño{1}(minced, ribs and seeds removed for less heat). Drain and rinse @black beans{1%box}. Drain half the @corn{1%can} (use rest as you like). Lightly crush @tortilla chips{1.5%oz}(lightly crushed).

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pot{} over medium heat. Add bell pepper, onion, garlic, jalapeño (to taste), and @Mexican spice blend{1%tsp}. Cook until softened and lightly browned, ~{5-6%minutes}, tossing.

Add ½ box of @crushed tomatoes{1%box}, 3 cups water, and @veggie stock concentrate{2} to same #pot{}. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and reduce to a simmer. Cook until liquid is slightly reduced and flavors have come together, about ~{10%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir black beans and corn into same pot. Continue simmering until warmed through, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

While soup is simmering, halve, pit, and scoop flesh from @avocado{1}(halved and pitted). Chop into cubes.

Divide soup between #bowls{}, then top with avocado, @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}, and tortilla chips.